
[1]galenical

   GALEN'ICAL, a. Pertaining to or containing galena.

   1. [from Galen, the physician.] Relating to Galen or his principles and
   method of treating diseases. The galenic remedies consist of
   preparations of herbs and roots, by infusion, decoction, &c. The
   chimical remedies consist of preparations by means of calcination,
   digestion, fermentation, &c.
